Package: pheprobAoU
Type: Package
Title: Calculate PheProb (Phenotype Probabilities) Using All of Us EHR Data
Version: 1.2.0
Author: Alireza Ehteshami [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0009-0001-9637-1695>)
Maintainer: Alireza Ehteshami <alireza.ehteshami@emory.edu>
Authors@R: 
    person("Alireza", "Ehteshami", email = "alireza.ehteshami@emory.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0001-9637-1695"))
Description: Implements the PheProb methodology (Sinnott et al., 2018) using binomial 
    mixture models for probabilistic phenotyping with electronic health record (EHR) 
    data from the All of Us Research Program. Features direct SQL queries with concept 
    hierarchy expansion and realistic healthcare utilization measurement. Includes 
    automatic concept expansion via OMOP concept_ancestor relationships, source-coded 
    condition counting, and general population cohorts for proper case/control mixture. 
    Provides true phenotype probabilities P(Y=1|S,C) with realistic disease prevalence 
    (15-25%) and excellent model performance. See Sinnott et al. (2018) 
    <doi:10.1093/jamia/ocy056>.
